  "prompt": "Why do I always feel a headache?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear that you're experiencing frequent headaches. There are many potential causes, including:\n\n- **Stress and tension:** Emotional stress or tension can lead to tension-type headaches.\n- **Dehydration:** Not drinking enough water can trigger headaches.\n- **Poor posture:** Straining your neck or back can contribute to headache pain.\n- **Sleep issues:** Both lack of sleep and irregular sleep patterns can cause headaches.\n- **Eye strain:** Extended screen time or improper eyewear can lead to headaches.\n- **Dietary factors:** Certain foods, caffeine withdrawal, or irregular eating patterns may be triggers.\n- **Medical conditions:** Migraines, sinus infections, or other underlying health issues might be responsible.\n\nIt's important to consult with a healthcare professional to discuss your symptoms in detail. They can help identify the underlying cause and recommend appropriate treatments or lifestyle changes to alleviate your headaches.",
